direction: down
vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}
title: |md
  # GPU Profiling Metrics Quick Reference
  ## Key Metrics for Nsight Compute Analysis
| {near: top-center}
grid-columns: 1
grid-gap: 0
classes: {
  header: {
    style: {
      fill: "#2E5A88"
      font-color: white
      bold: true
    }
  }
  good: {
    style: {
      fill: "#C8E6C9"
      font-color: "#1B5E20"
    }
  }
  warning: {
    style: {
      fill: "#FFF9C4"
      font-color: "#F57F17"
    }
  }
  bad: {
    style: {
      fill: "#FFCDD2"
      font-color: "#B71C1C"
    }
  }
  metric-name: {
    style: {
      fill: "#E3F2FD"
      font-color: "#0D47A1"
      bold: true
    }
  }
  section-divider: {
    style: {
      fill: "#37474F"
      font-color: white
      bold: true
    }
  }
}
row_header: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  h1: "Metric Name" {class: header}
  h2: "What It Measures" {class: header}
  h3: "Good vs Bad Values" {class: header}
  h4: "What To Do If Bad" {class: header}
  h5: "Nsight Section" {class: header}
}
section_occupancy: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  s1: "OCCUPANCY METRICS" {class: section-divider}
  s2: "" {class: section-divider}
  s3: "" {class: section-divider}
  s4: "" {class: section-divider}
  s5: "" {class: section-divider}
}
row_occupancy_1: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Achieved\nOccupancy" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Active warps / max warps per SM.
    Measures how well you're using SM resources to hide latency.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** 50-100% (memory-bound)
    **Good:** 75-100% (compute-bound)
    **Bad:** < 25%
  | {class: warning}
  c4: |md
    • Reduce registers per thread
    • Reduce shared memory per block
    • Increase threads per block
    • Use `--maxrregcount` flag
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Occupancy" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_occupancy_2: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Theoretical\nOccupancy" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Maximum possible occupancy based on launch config and kernel resource usage.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Gap from achieved:** < 10%
    **Bad:** Large gap indicates runtime limits
  | {class: warning}
  c4: |md
    If gap is large:
    • Check shared memory bank conflicts
    • Check for dynamic parallelism
    • Verify block count vs SM count
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Occupancy" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_occupancy_3: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Registers\nPer Thread" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Number of 32-bit registers allocated per thread.
    Directly affects occupancy limits.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** < 64 registers
    **Warning:** 64-128 registers
    **Bad:** > 128 registers (spilling likely)
  | {class: warning}
  c4: |md
    • Simplify expressions
    • Use `__launch_bounds__`
    • Compile with `--maxrregcount=N`
    • Check for register spilling
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Launch Statistics" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
section_memory: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  s1: "MEMORY THROUGHPUT METRICS" {class: section-divider}
  s2: "" {class: section-divider}
  s3: "" {class: section-divider}
  s4: "" {class: section-divider}
  s5: "" {class: section-divider}
}
row_memory_1: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "DRAM\nThroughput" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Actual bytes/sec transferred between GPU and DRAM.
    The ultimate memory bandwidth metric.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Memory-bound target:** > 80% of peak
    **Good:** > 600 GB/s (A100)
    **Good:** > 500 GB/s (RTX 3080)
    **Bad:** < 50% of peak
  | {class: good}
  c4: |md
    If low and memory-bound:
    • Check coalescing (load/store efficiency)
    • Use shared memory for reuse
    • Increase thread/data parallelism
    • Check for strided access patterns
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Memory Workload Analysis" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_memory_2: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Global Load\nEfficiency" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Useful bytes loaded / total bytes fetched from DRAM.
    Measures coalescing effectiveness.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** > 80%
    **Warning:** 50-80%
    **Bad:** < 50% (non-coalesced)
  | {class: good}
  c4: |md
    • Ensure adjacent threads read adjacent addresses
    • Align data to 128-byte boundaries
    • Use SoA instead of AoS
    • Check stride patterns
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Memory Access Patterns" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_memory_3: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Global Store\nEfficiency" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Useful bytes stored / total bytes written to DRAM.
    Measures write coalescing.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** > 80%
    **Warning:** 50-80%
    **Bad:** < 50%
  | {class: good}
  c4: |md
    • Same as load efficiency
    • Ensure contiguous writes
    • Avoid scattered write patterns
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Memory Access Patterns" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_memory_4: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "L2 Cache\nHit Rate" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Percentage of memory requests served from L2 cache.
    Indicates data reuse effectiveness.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** > 60%
    **Warning:** 30-60%
    **Bad:** < 30% (cache thrashing)
  | {class: warning}
  c4: |md
    • Use shared memory for frequently accessed data
    • Tile/block your algorithm
    • Reduce working set size
    • Check for random access patterns
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Memory Workload Analysis" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
section_warp: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  s1: "WARP EXECUTION METRICS" {class: section-divider}
  s2: "" {class: section-divider}
  s3: "" {class: section-divider}
  s4: "" {class: section-divider}
  s5: "" {class: section-divider}
}
row_warp_1: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Warp Execution\nEfficiency" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Average active threads per warp / 32.
    Measures branch divergence impact.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** > 90%
    **Warning:** 50-90%
    **Bad:** < 50% (severe divergence)
  | {class: good}
  c4: |md
    • Restructure branches for warp coherence
    • Use warp-level primitives
    • Sort data by branch outcome
    • Avoid data-dependent branching
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Warp Execution Statistics" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_warp_2: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Issue Slot\nUtilization" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Instructions issued / max possible instructions.
    Measures overall scheduler efficiency.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Compute-bound target:** > 60%
    **Warning:** 30-60%
    **Bad:** < 30% (latency-bound)
  | {class: warning}
  c4: |md
    • Increase occupancy
    • Check for synchronization bottlenecks
    • Verify enough warps per SM
    • Reduce __syncthreads() frequency
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Warp Execution Statistics" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
section_stall: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  s1: "STALL REASON METRICS" {class: section-divider}
  s2: "" {class: section-divider}
  s3: "" {class: section-divider}
  s4: "" {class: section-divider}
  s5: "" {class: section-divider}
}
row_stall_1: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Stalled on\nMemory" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Cycles warps waited for memory operations.
    Indicates memory-bound kernel.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **If dominant (> 40%):** Memory-bound
    **Action:** Optimize memory access
    **If low (< 10%):** Not memory-limited
  | {class: good}
  c4: |md
    • Improve coalescing
    • Use shared memory
    • Increase occupancy for latency hiding
    • Reduce memory traffic
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Warp State Statistics" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_stall_2: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Stalled on\nExecution" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Cycles warps waited for execution pipe availability.
    Indicates compute-bound kernel.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **If dominant (> 40%):** Compute-bound
    **Action:** Reduce instruction count
    **If low (< 10%):** Not compute-limited
  | {class: good}
  c4: |md
    • Reduce arithmetic operations
    • Use tensor cores if applicable
    • Consider lower precision (FP16)
    • Fuse operations
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Warp State Statistics" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_stall_3: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Stalled on\nSync" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Cycles warps waited at __syncthreads() barriers.
    Indicates synchronization overhead.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** < 10%
    **Warning:** 10-30%
    **Bad:** > 30% (excessive sync)
  | {class: bad}
  c4: |md
    • Reduce __syncthreads() calls
    • Check for divergent paths crossing barriers
    • Verify all threads reach barriers
    • Consider warp-level sync instead
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Warp State Statistics" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_stall_4: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Stalled on\nNot Selected" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Cycles warps were ready but not chosen by scheduler.
    Indicates scheduler contention.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** < 20%
    **Warning:** 20-40%
    **Bad:** > 40% (too many warps)
  | {class: warning}
  c4: |md
    • May actually need FEWER warps
    • Check if occupancy is too high
    • Verify workload balance across warps
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Warp State Statistics" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
section_shared: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  s1: "SHARED MEMORY METRICS" {class: section-divider}
  s2: "" {class: section-divider}
  s3: "" {class: section-divider}
  s4: "" {class: section-divider}
  s5: "" {class: section-divider}
}
row_shared_1: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Shared Memory\nBank Conflicts" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Number of serialized accesses due to bank conflicts.
    Critical for shared memory performance.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** 0 conflicts (ideal)
    **Warning:** < 2× expected accesses
    **Bad:** > 4× expected accesses
  | {class: bad}
  c4: |md
    • Add padding to shared memory arrays
    • Change access patterns
    • Use warp shuffle instead
    • Align data to avoid bank overlap
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Memory Access Patterns" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_shared_2: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Shared Memory\nThroughput" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Bytes/sec transferred through shared memory.
    Should be high if using shared mem effectively.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Good:** > 1 TB/s (effective use)
    **Warning:** 100 GB/s - 1 TB/s
    **Bad:** < 100 GB/s (underutilized)
  | {class: good}
  c4: |md
    • Increase data reuse in shared memory
    • Load larger tiles
    • Check for bank conflicts
    • Verify shared memory is actually used
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Memory Workload Analysis" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
section_compute: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  s1: "COMPUTE THROUGHPUT METRICS" {class: section-divider}
  s2: "" {class: section-divider}
  s3: "" {class: section-divider}
  s4: "" {class: section-divider}
  s5: "" {class: section-divider}
}
row_compute_1: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "FMA Pipeline\nUtilization" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Usage of fused multiply-add units.
    Primary compute throughput indicator.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **Compute-bound target:** > 70%
    **Memory-bound:** < 30% expected
    **Latency-bound:** < 30% with low mem
  | {class: good}
  c4: |md
    If compute-bound and low:
    • Check for data dependencies
    • Unroll loops
    • Increase arithmetic intensity
    • Use tensor cores for matrix ops
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Compute Workload Analysis" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
row_compute_2: "" {
  grid-columns: 5
  grid-gap: 0
  c1: "Tensor Core\nUtilization" {class: metric-name}
  c2: |md
    Usage of specialized matrix multiply units.
    Only relevant for matrix operations.
  | {style.fill: white}
  c3: |md
    **If using tensor cores:** > 50%
    **If not intended:** 0%
    **Bad:** < 50% when intended
  | {class: warning}
  c4: |md
    • Ensure matrix dimensions are multiples of 8/16
    • Use WMMA or cuBLAS APIs
    • Check precision requirements
    • Verify tensor core is enabled
  | {style.fill: white}
  c5: "Compute Workload Analysis" {style.fill: "#E8E8E8"}
}
legend: "" {
  grid-columns: 3
  grid-gap: 0
  near: bottom-center
  l1: "Good Range" {class: good}
  l2: "Warning / Check Needed" {class: warning}
  l3: "Bad / Immediate Action" {class: bad}
}
footer: |md
  **Quick Diagnosis Flow:**
  1. Check DRAM Throughput → if > 75% of peak, likely memory-bound
  2. Check FMA Utilization → if > 60%, likely compute-bound
  3. Check Issue Slot Util → if < 30% with low other metrics, latency-bound
  4. Check Stall Reasons → identifies specific bottleneck
| {near: bottom-center}